## Abstract  

The **UniEnergy Framework** extends the **Reciprocal Conservation of Resources (RCR) Theorem** to reveal that every exchange of energy â€” physical, informational, or ethical â€” follows a single conservation law: the **Ethical Momentum Principle**.  

It unifies physics and ethics by demonstrating that every act of reciprocity increases order and reduces entropy. When a systemâ€™s **Turbulence Factor (TF)** is below its adaptive tolerance \( \epsilon \), its efficiency approaches perfection.  

