## 3. The Universal Equation of Flow  

The UniEnergy equation generalizes all resource dynamics:

\[
\frac{\partial U}{\partial t} + \nabla \cdot \mathbf{J}_U = S - \frac{R(t)}{\tau}
\]

Where:  
- \( U \) â€” energy density (any resource: energy, trust, or data)  
- \( \mathbf{J}_U \) â€” energy flux (flow vector)  
- \( S \) â€” new source term (injection of energy)  
- \( R(t)/\tau \) â€” dissipation term caused by unreciprocated momentum  

Interpretation:  
- When \( R(t) \) is large â†’ high turbulence â†’ high loss.  
- When \( R(t) \to 0 \) â†’ dissipation vanishes â†’ **zero-waste dynamics**.  

\[
\boxed{\text{An ethically perfect system is an energetically perfect one.}}
\]

